			<h1>Reference Guide</h1>
			<a id="CreatingAShow"></a>
			<h2>Creating A Show</h2>
			<p>
				First, you will need to login. If you do not have an account, you can <a href="/signup">sign up</a>. After you are logged in, you will see a list of your existing shows. This is where you can create a new show or edit existing shows. Creating or editing shows will open up the Editor.
			</p>

			<a id="Editor"></a>
			<h2>The Editor</h2>
			<p>
				The editor is where the magic happens. The editor is broken into 4 sections:
				<ol>
					<li><em>Field</em>: the grid that represents the marching field</li>
					<li><em>Header Panel</em>: sits above the <em>Field</em></li>
					<li><em>Toolbar</em>: sits to the right of the <em>Field</em> and contains the different <em>Features</em></li>
					<li><em>Control Panel</em>: site below the <em>Field</em> and will be populated with different inputs and controls based on the selected <em>Feature</em></li>
				</ol>
			</p>

			<h2>Helpers</h2>
			<a id="Helpers"></a>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-4">
					<h3>Pan / Zoom</h3>
					<p>
						<code>shift + [scroll]</code> over the <em>Field</em> will Pan<br />
						<code>alt + [scroll]</code> over the <em>Field</em> will Zoom<br />
						Click the <code>[<span class="fa fa-search"></span>]</code> button in the <em>Toolbar</em> to reset the <em>Field's</em> Pan/Zoom.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4">
					<h3>Snap To Grid</h3>
					<p>
						Holding <code>shift</code> will activate "Snap-to-Grid" for the following situations:
						<ul>
							<li>Adding Performers</li>
							<li>Drag / Drop Performers</li>
							<li>Drawing Reference Objects</li>
						</ul>
					</p>
				</div>
